From 5d255112d268f9d5200780d7a847d6a0132ec88e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 14:10:40 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Diff sub-mode: collapsable file cards + inline/side-by-side
 toggle
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Per-file collapse:

- Click `.krt-pr-diff-section-head` toggles a `.collapsed` class on
  the section. CSS hides `.krt-pr-diff-section-body` while collapsed.
- Caret rotates via CSS transition.
- `collapsedDiffFiles: Set<string>` is session-scoped — collapse
  state survives sub-mode switches but resets on PR reopen.
- Click handler skips when the target is inside a `<label> / <input>
  / <button> / <a>` so the existing Reviewed checkbox keeps working.

Inline / side-by-side toggle:

- New `.krt-pr-diff-topbar` above the file-tree+stack grid with a
  small segmented control.
- `diffRenderMode` persisted in `IStorageService` under
  `krt.pr.diffMode.v1` (APPLICATION/MACHINE scope, like the
  reviewed-paths store).
- `KrtMonacoDiffView` accepts `renderSideBySide` in its options; the
  pane passes `this.diffRenderMode === 'side-by-side'` into both the
  main diff view and the tour mini-diffs.
- Toggle calls `renderLoaded(pr)` to rebuild — quickest path; the
  tradeoff is a brief flicker we accept for an infrequent action.
